    "**One important honesty note before you run this:** this compares NonZero's proposal mechanism against a MAZero-style random-sampling baseline under equal budget — it does **not** reproduce Table 1's exact reported numbers (697.1 vs 672.3), since that requires the full trained MCTS pipeline we haven't wired up. This is directionally consistent evidence (NonZero-style > MAZero-style, on the exact paper's hardest config), clearly labeled as toy-scale — the same honest framing that worked for Claim 1."
